transcript_text: Sam Altman killed millions of jobs with one insane update. He released GPT-5 today and literally made it free for all. Here are the 12 insane features of GPT-5 that you should try. Number 4 is my personal favorite. Let's get into it. Number 12. Smart reasoning mode. GPT-5 now routes your prompt through the best model based on complexity. If it's a simple ask, you get an answer instantly. If it's more complex, it slows down and thinks harder and then answers. No more picking the right model for right task bullshit. 11. Autopilot agents. GPT-5 can now handle an entire task from start to finish on its own. It researches online, analyzes images, writes the code and completes the job without follow-ups. It's like having a superhuman teammate. 10. One-prompt app builder. Say, build a flashcard site. Two minutes later, you're clicking through it. Live, working React app, real code, no dev needed. 9. Hyper-reliable answers. Hallucinations down 65%. Instead of guessing, it now asks smart follow-ups. 8. Vision plus video understanding. Snap a whiteboard scribble, GPT-5 gives you a clean project plan. It understands diagrams, video frames and ranks number one in vision benchmarks. 7. 256k context window. Paste a book, emails and meeting notes. GPT-5 keeps all of it in memory. No chunking, no forgetting. 6. Inbox plus calendar automation. It replies to emails, finds a free slot and books the meeting. Inbox zero is now background noise. 5. Thought outline peak. You can now preview what GPT-5 is thinking before it acts. Whether it's rewriting code or planning content, you see the logic first. 4. Smart personal memory. Tell it once, I'm flying Saturday. Next time, it shifts your schedule, preps your checklist and drafts you're out of office. It remembers and you're always in control. 3. Study plus learn mode. Say, teach me Bernoulli. It explains it out loud, shows a live sim and quizzes you. It's a private tutor in real time. 2. Built-in personalities plus themes. Pick a tone, sarcastic strategist, empathetic coach, whatever fits. No prompt tricks, just tap and switch. 1. Developer turbo pack. One API, three models. GPT-5, Mini, Nano. Nano is 25 times cheaper. You get control sliders, valid structured output and the highest SWE bench score in class. GPT-5 became your coder, tutor, planner, designer and strategist at the same time. Save this if you want to stay ahead. Follow for more because the upgrades aren't slowing down.
